english_poem_line: O Lord of the World, Jagannatha
Oh Lord, you are in everything
In Madhuban, the essence of divine play
The mind floats in devotion's essence
The radiance of the sun jewel
On the shore of dream ocean
Beauty of flowers, fruits and leaves
Union of soul and supreme soul
Bada Danda the path of devotion
Rath Yatra of the Great Lord
Wealth and grains of Lakshmi Puja
King of kings of Raja Parba
I shall tell the story of the ascetic woman
The ocean of love is deep
Service to people is service to God
The path is far and winding
The power of words is great
On the shore of dream ocean
The sky of words is vast
The rotation of time is endless
Sri Radha is symbol of love
The vast world is full of joy
The glory of language is great
The man of time is great
I wake up in the morning
The wild rose with pink hue
The great river of love flows
Where there is will there is way
Hard work is key to success
Dharma protects those who protect it
Too much greed brings no gain
No danger in company of saints
